      "id": "02bebeb1_7c41735d",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-http/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/participant/http/main/handler/ControlLoopElementHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "Hi Jim, If we pass the value from the thread response, then should we make this main thread wait until the http requests are finished executing for a single request? Future().get going to be blocking right?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6070,
        "name": "Ramesh Murugan Iyer",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.murugan.iyer@est.tech",
        "username": "rameshiyer27"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 17:27:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "34a8801b_6a2ab02f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bd7d59f9_e05218d2",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-http/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/participant/http/main/handler/ControlLoopElementHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 98,
      "message": "Kubernetes-participant and http-participant are using this same block of code to convert the node template's properties to the corresponding instances. Should we move this code to a different common module for both?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6070,
        "name": "Ramesh Murugan Iyer",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.murugan.iyer@est.tech",
        "username": "rameshiyer27"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 17:27:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e18059c0_b3e06b10",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d725b26e_3103764c",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-http/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/participant/http/main/handler/ControlLoopElementHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "ClHttpClient calls back into here to get the map via getRestResponseMap().  All I'm suggesting is to avoid that call by passing the map to the ClHttpClient constructor.  That would eliminate the need to make it static (unless there is more than one ControlLoopElementHandler), and it also provides better information encapsulation/hiding.\n\nThe behavior is the same with either approach, so no impact on threading.\n\nI reeeealy don't like static data, as it's basically just global data wrapped in a namespace (i.e., class).  You can find my comments about in at: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Policy+Project+Team+Developer+Contribution+Requirements",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 18:00:50.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "02bebeb1_7c41735d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "03f4289d_2c3b47c0",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-http/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/participant/http/main/handler/ControlLoopElementHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 98,
      "message": "makes sense to me",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-28 18:00:50.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "bd7d59f9_e05218d2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
